{"email":"tonyx122@icloud.com","unix_timestamp":1610982395,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"Jesus is the source of all things. 

Obedience is key for one to experience God’s power. Jesus demonstrates obedience to his mother( even though he stated his time hadn’t come yet)  His disciples show obedience too, no questions asked.John 2:1-7. We tend to ask a lot of questions when things don’t make sense. We must allow faith to flow and reveals its hidden miracles. 

John 3 Nicodemus deals with peer pressure. He was a teacher that was astounded by Jesus’s message but he feared what his fellow Pharisee would think so he approached Jesus at night to inquire more. How often do we allow peer pressure to keep our faith stagnant?"}

column14:
{"email":"auray1990@gmail.com","unix_timestamp":1610980158,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"John 1:1-4:- The Word preceded the beginning so, the Word is greater than the beginning and everything inside and after the beginning. So, the Word of God is greater than anyone/ system or being. 

Nothing can be created outside of the Word. The life I want, the future I want cannot be created outside of the Word.

I need the Word of God...period!"}

column28:
{"email":"Okerekechinelo@gmail.com","unix_timestamp":1610977255,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"John 2:11- The outcome of the first miracle was the revelation of God’s glory. God’s work in your life is to showcase God’s glory and inspire belief from the heart of others in God. 

When people see me, do they see the glory of God ? Does my life inspire others to believe in God?
There is no doubt that I experience the miraculous, as being alive is a miracle. But do I expressively attribute all credit and glory to God, for others to see and to understand the source?"}

column35:
{"email":"ogbdike@yahoo.com","unix_timestamp":1610976323,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"They asked for wine, but Jesus gave them something easy to get 'water'.
It was available but wine was not available or accessible.
&quot;Despise not the days of small beginnings&quot;. Because if we can be faithful while our handling water, it might just be our wine.
There's something in the process of being committed to our vision when it looks like is nothing happening. and the devil is saying &quot;Where is your God? I thought you asked God for wine, I thought God was goning do something? What good is it to just to have water?&quot;
It might still look like its water, but trust that God is a miracle working God. Keep in faith and dont doubt God and what looks like water right now can be the wine we were praying for."}

