column46:
{"email":"ogechiucheatu@gmail.com","unix_timestamp":1610975166,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"The verse that stood out to me was John 2 vs. 10 &quot;Everyone brings out the choice wine first and then the cheaper wine after the guests have had too much to drink; but you have saved the best till now.”

This let's me know that when God steps in, there is newness. He is God of the 11th hour and he saves the best for last. 

Ogechi U."}

column56:
{"email":"odebunmioluwabukola@gmail.com","unix_timestamp":1610974230,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"2 words that stood out to me from the three chapters; Obedience and Believing. For God to perform wonders in our lives, we must believe His word and obey His instructions. 

John 1:5 - “The light shines in the darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it.”
‭‭The word of God is light, and darkness cannot comprehend nor understand it. Therefore, if we have darkness in our hearts, the word of God cannot work in our lives."}

column86:
{"email":"raphaelnkemdilim@yahoo.co.uk","unix_timestamp":1610968068,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"Witnessing is a key part of God's approach to introducing the light to the world. 

Note that God could have sent Jesus Christ to the world without John to perform all miracles, but He sent John (a witness) first. 

This implies that witnessing is a big part of God's plan and a major expectation from us, to ensure the light continues to spread all through the world."}

column89:
{"email":"temitayo.oribabor@gmail.com","unix_timestamp":1610967423,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"Key areas that stood out are:
John1:45-51 The reason the disciples who met Jesus at the beginning were able to believe He was the son of man was because they had actually listened and believed the words of the prophets and Moses and allowed that to bring forth their faith. This reminded me of PWA's word yesterday on faith

John 3:26-30 We must all be clear on our assignments by God and not let ourselves be influenced by the wrong words. John was clear on his role which was why when Jesus started baptising people and John's followers came to complain He didn't let that influence him negatively"}

column91:
{"email":"emmanuel.olusuyi@hotmail.com","unix_timestamp":1610967302,"date_created":"Fri Jan 22 2021 19:44:26 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time)","comment":"Christ is all-sufficient, because of His fullness, we all have received and grace for grace. Everything I will ever need for life now and in eternity is all packaged in Jesus Christ.

Anyone who dismisses the testimonies of Christ adjudged God a liar. Life will be hidden from such a one and the wrath of God abides on such.

If He who comes from above dwells in me, dominion life becomes activated. Life with eternity in view goes live in me. My worldview seizes from being earthly, but rather eternal and wise."}

